# Quick Reference - Project Rules

One-line rules for quick lookup. See detailed files for explanations.

## Planning
- When planning implementation (UI flows, navigation, async-loaded screens), read **`DEV_GUIDELINES.md`** at the repository root alongside these rules.

## Client Version Gate
- After a breaking server/client change bump `MIN_CLIENT_VERSION` in server env (`.env`, `compose.prod.yaml`, VPS); see `versioning.mdc` § Client version gate for when to bump

## V2 Routing
- Every Tentura V2 GraphQL operation must be listed in `_tenturaDirectOperationNames` in `packages/client/lib/data/service/remote_api_client/build_client.dart` so the client hits `/api/v2/graphql` directly, not Hasura V1
- When adding a V2 query/mutation: add the client `.graphql` operation name to that set; ensure the V2 server schema exposes matching types/fields for everything the operation selects (see `DEV_GUIDELINES.md` § V2 direct routing)

## Real-Time Invalidation
- Server-pushed entity invalidation uses the existing V2 WebSocket (`/api/v2/ws`), NOT Hasura subscriptions or HTTP polling
- Data flow: PG trigger -> `PgNotificationService` (`entity_changes` channel) -> `WebsocketRouterBase` fan-out -> client `InvalidationService` -> repository `changes` stream -> cubit refetch
- When adding real-time updates for a new entity, follow the checklist in `DEV_GUIDELINES.md` section "Entity invalidation (real-time)"
- All client-side invalidation goes through `InvalidationService` (`packages/client/lib/data/service/invalidation_service.dart`); do NOT parse WS messages directly in repositories
- Server fan-out targets users by DB relationships (author, committer, sender/receiver); no client-side subscription registration in phase 1
- Server mutations wrap in `db.withMutatingUser(userId, ...)` to suppress echo back to originating user -- see `DEV_GUIDELINES.md` § Echo suppression
- Client uses `rxdart` `bufferTime` for debounced invalidation streams -- see `DEV_GUIDELINES.md` § Echo suppression

## Codegen
- Run `dart run build_runner build -d` after codegen changes
- Never commit `*.g.dart`, `*.freezed.dart`, `*.gr.dart`, `_g/`, `di.config.dart`
- Use Freezed for all domain entities and BLoC states
- Use extension types to wrap Ferry GraphQL types
- Router must be `@singleton` for Injectable

## Architecture
- **Inward dependencies:** outer layers depend on inner contracts (domain stays pure; data implements domain **ports** on the server)
- **Server domain:** use cases use **`domain/port/*`** only — verify with `rg "package:tentura_server/data/repository" packages/server/lib/domain` (should be empty)
- **`packages/tentura_lints` (`custom_lint` on client + server):** `no_domain_to_data_or_ui_import`, `no_cubit_to_data_service_import`, `no_map_dynamic_in_use_case_api`, `no_raw_graphql_in_dart`, `cubit_requires_use_case_for_multi_repos` — see **Static enforcement** in `architecture.mdc`
- Repositories return domain entities, never Ferry types or Drift models
- **Image / picker boundary:** repository pick APIs use domain **`ImagePicked`** (or equivalent); keep **`XFile`** and similar types inside **data** only
- Use cases orchestrate business logic; repositories handle remote/local I/O
- **Heavy cubits** (multi-repo / streams): inject a **`features/*/domain/use_case/*_case`** (`@singleton`), not six repositories
- Features are independent modules with data/domain/ui layers

## Injectable
- `@singleton` for use cases, global BLoC, services
- `@lazySingleton` for repositories, feature-specific services
- `@injectable` for regular factories
- Use `@module` abstract class for DI modules (providers, database, etc.)
- Use `@InjectableInit()` on `configureDependencies` function
- Use `order` parameter: 1 (Data) → 2 (Domain) → 3 (App) → 4 (UI)
- Constructor injection preferred, `GetIt.I<>()` acceptable in BLoC
- Use `@disposeMethod` for BLoC cleanup methods

## Freezed
- All domain entities use `@freezed`
- States extend `StateBase` and use Freezed
- Use `copyWith()` for immutable updates, never mutate directly
- Add `const ClassName._();` for custom methods
- Use `@Default()` for optional fields

## Ferry & GraphQL
- Write queries in `.graphql` files
- Use `GQueryNameReq()` for requests
- Access via `r.dataOrThrow(label: 'Label').field`
- Convert Ferry types → entities via extension type `toEntity()`
- Never expose Ferry types outside data layer
- Every Hasura custom scalar (`smallint`, `float8`, `uuid`, etc.) must have a `type_overrides` entry in both Ferry builder sections of `build.yaml`; without it, Ferry generates broken `G<Scalar>` wrappers — see `DEV_GUIDELINES.md` § "Ferry custom scalars"
- After overrides, register `Float8Serializer` and `SmallintSerializer` under `custom_serializers` (serializer_builder only): MeritRank `mr_*` → `mutual_score` fields often arrive as JSON strings; see `DEV_GUIDELINES.md` and `packages/server/WORKAROUNDS.md` section 3

## Repositories
- Return domain entities only
- Use `@lazySingleton` (or `@singleton` if needed)
- Extend `RemoteRepository` base for common patterns
- Separate local vs remote when needed
- All repos have mock implementations in `mock/` directory

## BLoC/Cubit
- States extend `StateBase` with `StateStatus` sealed class
- Use Freezed for state immutability (**including `ScreenState`** in `ui/bloc/screen_state.dart`)
- **Never mutate** `state` collections in place — `emit(state.copyWith(items: [...state.items, x]))`, new `Map` copies, etc.
- Prefer **use cases** for orchestration; thin single-repo cubits may use one repository
- **Do not** import `package:tentura/.../data/service/` from `ui/bloc/*_cubit.dart` (lint: `no_cubit_to_data_service_import`)
- Use `copyWith()` to update state
- Pattern match on `StateStatus` for status checks

## Exceptions
- Server: `ExceptionBase` with hierarchical codes (code spaces: 1000, 1100, 1200...)
- Client: `LocalizableException` with `toEn`/`toRu` for user-facing errors
- Use sealed classes for exception types
- Domain exceptions in domain layer, feature exceptions in feature domain

## State Management
- `StateBase` with `StateStatus` sealed class
- Status: `StateIsSuccess`, `StateIsLoading`, `StateHasError`, `StateIsNavigating`, `StateIsMessaging`
- Pattern match with `is` checks
- Localizable messages in `StateIsMessaging`

## Platform Abstraction
- Use conditional exports: `export 'native.dart' if (dart.library.js_interop) 'web.dart';`
- Base abstraction required, platform-specific implementations
- Pattern: `*_base.dart`, `*_native.dart`, `*_web.dart`

## Environment
- All config via `Env` class, never hardcode
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Support `Env.dev()`, `Env.prod()`, `Env.test()`
- Env is `@singleton` and injected everywhere

## Testing
- Mocks use `@Injectable(as: RealType, env: [Environment.test])`
- Mocks in `data/repository/mock/` directory
- **Shared fixtures** in `data/repository/mock/data/` — reuse in tests / stub defaults instead of ad-hoc empty maps
- Mocks implement full repository interface
- **CI:** `flutter analyze --fatal-infos` / `dart analyze --fatal-infos` run in the pipeline — fix new analyzer issues before merge

## File Naming
- Screens: `*_screen.dart` (triggers Auto Route)
- States: `*_state.dart` (use Freezed)
- Repositories: `*_repository.dart` (use Injectable)
- Models: `*_model.dart` (extension types)
- GraphQL: `*.graphql` in `data/gql/`

## Auto Route
- Annotate screens: `@RoutePage()`
- Screens implement `AutoRouteWrapper` for BLoC setup
- Use `wrappedRoute()` to provide BLoC/Cubit before build
- Use `@PathParam('id')` and `@QueryParam('key')` for parameters
- Register in `root_router.dart` with `AutoRoute(page: MyRoute.page)`
- Router class must be `@singleton`

## Sealed Classes
- Use for closed type hierarchies (`StateStatus`, `ExceptionCodes`, `RepositoryEvent`)
- Prefer sealed over abstract for fixed sets
- Enable exhaustive pattern matching

## Extension Types
- Use for Ferry model wrappers (zero-cost)
- Implement `toEntity()` conversion method
- Keep wrappers thin

## Factory Methods
- Use `@FactoryMethod(preResolve: true)` for async initialization
- Keep factory methods focused
- Document initialization requirements

## Monorepo
- Shared domain in `lib/` (root package)
- Packages: `client/`, `server/`, `widgetbook/`
- Packages depend on root, not each other
- Independent versioning per package
- Bump **patch** for bug fixes; **minor** for new features; **major** for breaking changes (semver)

## Constants & Utilities
- Use `k*` prefix for constants (kPathHome, kPaddingSmallH, kSpacingMedium)
- Define in `consts.dart`, export from root package
- Use `commonScreenBlocListener` for standard BLoC state handling (navigation, messaging, errors)
- Constants: `kPadding*`, `kSpacing*`, `kPath*`, `kQuery*`

## Screen Patterns
- Implement `AutoRouteWrapper` interface
- Use `wrappedRoute()` to wrap with `BlocProvider`/`MultiBlocProvider`
- Use `commonScreenBlocListener` in `BlocListener` for standard behavior
- Access BLoC via `GetIt.I<>()` or `context.read<>()` in build method

## Typography & Responsive
- Use `TenturaText.*` / `theme.textTheme.*` — never inline `fontSize` in `features/**` or `ui/**` (see `no_inline_font_size` + design doc)
- Floors: metadata 13, body 15, label 15, navLabel 12.5; sizes 8/10/11/12 banned in `features/**` and `ui/**`
- WindowClass: &lt;600 compact, 600–839 regular, &gt;=840 expanded; density via `context.tt` tokens, not type scale
- Never override `textScaler` globally; let Flutter handle a11y scaling
- `web/index.html` viewport: `width=device-width`, `initial-scale=1`, `viewport-fit=cover`; no `maximum-scale`, no `user-scalable=no`

## Server GraphQL (graphql_schema2)
- NEVER call `.nonNullable()` on `GraphQLListType` -- triggers library bug, see `packages/server/WORKAROUNDS.md` section 2
- Nullable scalar arguments + null values crash validation -- workaround in `_NullSafeGraphQL`, see `packages/server/WORKAROUNDS.md` section 1
- Use `GraphQLListType(innerType.nonNullable())` for `[T!]` arguments; enforce list non-null in `fromArgs`
- Define list arguments as `InputField*` classes (pattern: `input_field_*.dart` as `part of '_input_types.dart'`) with `field` + `fromArgs` like `InputFieldPolling`
- `fromArgs` handles `List<String>.from(args[key]! as List)` -- safe cast at the resolver layer
- NEVER add field-name-specific coercion hacks in `graphql_controller.dart`; fix at the type definition layer

## Library Bug Workarounds
- When a bug is **proven** to be in a third-party library, **cannot** be fixed by upgrading, and requires a workaround: document it in the relevant package's `WORKAROUNDS.md` and add a one-line pointer here
- When touching code that may trigger a documented workaround, read the corresponding `WORKAROUNDS.md` section first

## Rule Maintenance
- If you observe significant architectural patterns in the codebase that contradict these rules, notify the user
- Suggest updating `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files when patterns diverge consistently
- Examples: new codegen tools, different layer structure, alternative state management patterns
- When suggesting updates, provide specific examples of the divergence found
